                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.62/50.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">O’Shaughnessy</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-13T14:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 13, 1914, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>849. The German Minister informs me that a German subject named Radke has been
                    kidnapped by rebel forces near Guaymas, Sonora, and requests me to bring the
                    matter to your attention and to request you to make representations to the rebel
                    authorities to the end that Radke be liberated immediately and permitted to
                    follow his lawful occupation. He further asked me to request President to
                    impress upon the rebel authorities in question that German subjects within their
                    jurisdiction must be treated with the same respect and consideration as are
                    other foreigners and be allowed to follow their lawful occupations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson O’Shaughnessy</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
